Found most of this stuff on some Chinese forum (bbs.pinggu.org), so respect to all the guys there (plus to Google Translate). I've added all 4 executables (small, IC, SE, MP) for x86 and x64 systems, plus pregenerated the license files. Not sure if serials & codes can be blocked by Stata Corp., all I can say is that they work now. You can also find them below. All you need to do is to extract the main archive, and then just choose the flavor of Stata you want (=extract its executable and license). No installation necessary.

Apparently the MP version needs this: Microsoft Visual C++ 2008 SP1 Redistributable Package, although I didn't have to install anything
x86: http://www.microsoft.com/download/en/details.aspx?id=5582
x64: http://www.microsoft.com/download/en/details.aspx?id=2092

Everything is up-to-date as of today (Oct 20), and I've encountered no problems when updating. In case you want to recreate the STATA.LIC file using your own information, delete it and use the following:
